The objective is to segment Town Hall (Mairie) accounts so they can manage specific municipalities (communes). They will be able to upload PLUi/PLU documents associated with their city, and configure a custom AI Prompt used exclusively when HEUREKA analyzes properties within that city.

## 1. Database Schema Updates (`packages/db`)
- **`townHallDocumentsTable`**:
  - [NEW] Add column `commune: text("commune")` indicating to which city the PDF document applies.
- **[NEW] `townHallPromptsTable`**:
  - Create a new Drizzle table to store custom prompts tailored per commune: [id](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/services/parcel.ts#281-299), `commune` (unique), `content` (custom instructions), `updatedAt`.
- *Action:* Run `drizzle-kit push` to apply schema updates without losing existing users.

## 2. Backend Routes (`api-server`)
- **[routes/mairie.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/mairie.ts)**:
