## 4. AI Pipeline Injection ([routes/documents.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/documents.ts) / [pluAnalysis.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/services/pluAnalysis.ts))
- During CERFA analysis, the system already identifies the `city` from geocoding.
- **PLU Documents Fetch**: Instead of fetching documents by `req.user.id` (which is the citizen uploader), the API will query `townHallDocumentsTable` where `commune = geocode.city`.
- **System Prompt Fetch**: The API will query `townHallPromptsTable` for the corresponding `geocode.city`. If found, it will inject these *Mairie-defined* custom instructions into the OpenAI context, falling back to the default global prompt otherwise.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> User Review: Please confirm the approach of binding Documents and Prompts strictly to the `city` text matching the Geocoder. It's the most robust way to decouple the citizen who submits a file from the Mairie who configures the local urban rules!
